{
 "name": "RPlog_Discussion_NRI",
 "title": "A Discussion at NRI",
 "summary": "Aboard the New Republic carrier NRSC Deliverance, NRI officer Voren Nadil hands Xanatos encrypted recordings of recent prisoner interviews, then the agents, joined by Dayna and the white-robed analyst Kathryn, retire to the guest intelligence section to study them over drinks. Voren projects a holo of the Imperial Admiral Cimbar and shares intelligence on the man's tactics, and the group turns to debating where the Republic should strike next. Voren favors hitting the relatively undefended naval station and OSG at O'paal, where their rivals from Bofo are berthed, while Xanatos argues for a series of hit-and-run raids on lightly guarded worlds like Trandosha, Kessel, and Athaniss to force the Empire to reposition its fleets away from Dreven and Selene. Kathryn weighs both options, noting the risk that provoking the Empire could draw its Death Star and main fleet toward Calamari or Corellia. They agree the final operational call rests with the Navy, and resolve to forward both sides of the strategic argument so the admirals can decide.",
